In the present case, from the facts and submissions 
referred above
, it transpires that young bride has not able to survive her married life for even seven months. The cause of death has been opined to be 'Asphyxia' due to ante-mortem hanging. Bail application of co-accused Ramniwas (father-in-law of deceased) has already been rejected by co-ordinate Bench, still there is a substance in the argument of learned counsel for applicant that present applicant is a student who is in jail since 23.12.2021 as well as that the nature of allegations appears to be omnibus and similar to all the accused persons.
